HTML - Hyper text Markup language

* To create a web pages
* its Not a programming language
* its a markup language
* Every website can start with HTML

1) Heading - h1 to h6 - h

2) paragraph - p

3) hr

4) br

5) Text formatting - u, b or strong, i, mark, sub and sup

6) Anchor tag - a

7) Image tag - img

8) list - order list and unorder list

9) Tables - th, tr and td

10) forms - Inputs, labels, placeholder, required

11) media elements - video and Audio

12) Sematic tags - header, footer, nav, main, section


CSS - Cascading Style Sheet

1) Types of CSS
i - inline
ii - internal
iii - External
inline > internal > external

2) CSS Synatax
 selector{
    property:value;
 }

3) Types of selector
i - element selector - h1, h2 and p
ii - Class selector - (.) - Multiple types can use a same class name
iii - Id selector - (#) - Unique, Only one time can use the same Id name
iv - Universal selector - (*) -  To apply the site
v - Group selector - same class name or id contains different tags, we wnat to same style means use with group select

4) Colors and Background
    color: red;
    background-color: green;
    background-image: url(./Assets/Spider-man.jpeg);
    background-repeat: no-repeat;
    background-size: cover;
    background-position: center;

5) Text Styling
    font-family: Verdana, Geneva, Tahoma, sans-serif;
    font-size: 20px;
    text-align: center;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    text-decoration: line-through;
    font-weight: 800;
    line-height: 1;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
    
6) box Modeling
   i - margin
  ii - border   
 iii - padding
  iv - content

7) Flex (Display)
1. Flex Direction - row, row-reverse, coloumn, coloumn-reverse
2. Justify content - (X) - Start, end, center, space-around, space-between, space-evenly
3. Align items - (Y) - Start, end, center
4. flex Wrap - no-wrap, wrap, wrap-reverse
5. Align content (Y) - (Whenever wrap will enable then only Align content will work) - Start, end, center, space-around, space-between, space-evenly
6. Gap - to be assign with values (px,cm,m,em,%)
7. Flex (on items) - only use with flex 1 property
8. order - Change the visual order 

8) Position
  i - static (default)
 ii - Relative
iii - Absolute
 iv - fixed
  v - Sticky

  